        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-04-19T16:40:49+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-19T16:40:49+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-19T07:10:49Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-19T07:10:49Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high pressure system is centred over the Bight and a weakening trough lies over the eastern districts. The trough will clear to the east this evening and the high will move southeastwards overnight to be centred southeast of Tasmania late Monday morning. The high will continue to extend a ridge over SA early next week ahead of a cold front expected to move across the south of SA late Tuesday and early Wednesday. Another high will move across waters to the south later Wednesday and will be centred southeast of Tasmania late Thursday morning.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
